what is the best way to switch the default to a different 
terminal emulator, e.g. *lxterminal*. I could not find a relevant line in
the configuration file.</description><pubDate>Sun, 10 Nov 2013 15:12:17 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2857/how-do-i-change-the-default-terminal-emulator/</guid></item><item><title>Answer by GermainZ for &lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;Alt + Enter&lt;/code&gt; starts &lt;em&gt;xterm&lt;/em&gt;; I was wondering 
what is the best way to switch the default to a different 
terminal emulator, e.g. &lt;em&gt;lxterminal&lt;/em&gt;. I could not find a relevant line in
the configuration file.&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2857/how-do-i-change-the-default-terminal-emulator/?answer=2858#post-id-2858</link><description>Check the man page for i3-sensible-terminal (````man i3-sensible-terminal````).
You can also modify this line in your i3 config: ````bindsym $mod+Return exec i3-sensible-terminal````</description><pubDate>Sun, 10 Nov 2013 15:17:08 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2857/how-do-i-change-the-default-terminal-emulator/?answer=2858#post-id-2858</guid></item></channel></rss>